msgstr "Is it really free?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. The free version lets you run full tournaments with up to 10 players per event. Pro (€79/year) removes the player limit and adds PGN games, photo galleries, and advanced exports."
msgstr "Yes. The free version lets you run full tournaments with up to 10 players per event. Pro (€79/year) removes the player limit and adds PGN games, photo galleries, and advanced exports."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "How do I install it?"
msgstr "How do I install it?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Download the plugin from the Download page, then in WordPress go to Plugins → Add New → Upload Plugin. Choose the ZIP file, install, and activate. After activation, go to Settings → Permalinks and click Save."
msgstr "Download the plugin from the Download page, then in WordPress go to Plugins → Add New → Upload Plugin. Choose the ZIP file, install, and activate. After activation, go to Settings → Permalinks and click Save."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "How many players can I add?"
msgstr "How many players can I add?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Free: up to 10 players per tournament. Pro: unlimited players."
msgstr "Free: up to 10 players per tournament. Pro: unlimited players."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Can I edit or delete a player after adding them?"
msgstr "Can I edit or delete a player after adding them?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. You can edit name, rating, and nationality at any time. You can delete a player only if they have not yet been paired in any round."
msgstr "Yes. You can edit name, rating, and nationality at any time. You can delete a player only if they have not yet been paired in any round."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "What if I enter a wrong result or make a mistake?"
msgstr "What if I enter a wrong result or make a mistake?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Use \"Undo current round\" to cancel the last generated round. You can then correct results and regenerate. No data is lost."
msgstr "Use \"Undo current round\" to cancel the last generated round. You can then correct results and regenerate. No data is lost."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "How does Swiss pairing work?"
msgstr "How does Swiss pairing work?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Players with the same score are paired against each other. Chess Podium generates pairings automatically. The engine is practical for club events; FIDE-advanced mode is on the roadmap."
msgstr "Players with the same score are paired against each other. Chess Podium generates pairings automatically. The engine is practical for club events; FIDE-advanced mode is on the roadmap."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "What is Round Robin?"
msgstr "What is Round Robin?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Round Robin means everyone plays everyone. Choose this when creating the tournament if you have a small group (typically under 12 players) and want all possible games."
msgstr "Round Robin means everyone plays everyone. Choose this when creating the tournament if you have a small group (typically under 12 players) and want all possible games."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "What tiebreakers are supported?"
msgstr "What tiebreakers are supported?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Buchholz, Sonneborn-Berger, rating, and direct encounter. You can set the order when creating the tournament."
msgstr "Buchholz, Sonneborn-Berger, rating, and direct encounter. You can set the order when creating the tournament."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "How do players see pairings and standings?"
msgstr "How do players see pairings and standings?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Share the live tournament URL (e.g. yoursite.com/torneo/). Players can view current standings, round pairings, and results on any device. No login required."
msgstr "Share the live tournament URL (e.g. yoursite.com/torneo/). Players can view current standings, round pairings, and results on any device. No login required."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Can I import players from Excel or CSV?"
msgstr "Can I import players from Excel or CSV?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. Use the bulk CSV import. Format: name;rating or name;rating;fide_id;country. The first row can be a header."
msgstr "Yes. Use the bulk CSV import. Format: name;rating or name;rating;fide_id;country. The first row can be a header."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Can I import players from FIDE?"
msgstr "Can I import players from FIDE?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. Enter a FIDE ID and Chess Podium fetches name, rating, and nationality from the official FIDE database."
msgstr "Yes. Enter a FIDE ID and Chess Podium fetches name, rating, and nationality from the official FIDE database."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Can I show past tournaments on my homepage?"
msgstr "Can I show past tournaments on my homepage?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. Use the archive widget or shortcode to display your club's tournament history on any page."
msgstr "Yes. Use the archive widget or shortcode to display your club's tournament history on any page."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Can I add tournaments from other software (Vega, Swiss Manager)?"
msgstr "Can I add tournaments from other software (Vega, Swiss Manager)?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. If the tournament is already published elsewhere, you can add it as an \"external tournament\" with a link. It will appear in the same layout as Chess Podium tournaments."
msgstr "Yes. If the tournament is already published elsewhere, you can add it as an \"external tournament\" with a link. It will appear in the same layout as Chess Podium tournaments."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "How does the Pro license work?"
msgstr "How does the Pro license work?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Pro is €79/year. After purchase you receive a license key by email. Enter it in Chess Podium → License. The license is validated periodically. One license per site."
msgstr "Pro is €79/year. After purchase you receive a license key by email. Enter it in Chess Podium → License. The license is validated periodically. One license per site."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Can I use Pro on multiple sites?"
msgstr "Can I use Pro on multiple sites?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Each site needs its own license. Contact us for multi-site or club federation pricing."
msgstr "Each site needs its own license. Contact us for multi-site or club federation pricing."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Will there be a desktop app?"
msgstr "Will there be a desktop app?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. Chess Podium Desktop for Windows and macOS is planned for the future."
msgstr "Yes. Chess Podium Desktop for Windows and macOS is planned for the future."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Does it work on mobile?"
msgstr "Does it work on mobile?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. The admin panel and public tournament pages are responsive. Players can follow pairings and standings on their phone."
msgstr "Yes. The admin panel and public tournament pages are responsive. Players can follow pairings and standings on their phone."

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Can I print the pairing sheet?"
msgstr "Can I print the pairing sheet?"

#: page-faq.php
msgid "Yes. Use \"Generate round and print pairings\" to create a round and open a printable sheet ready to post on the wall."
msgstr "Yes. Use \"Generate round and print pairings\" to create a round and open a printable sheet ready to post on the wall."

